9727

9728<h2>

9729How to Choose the Perfect Bridge Kitchen Faucet</h2>

9730

9731

9732<p>

9733Looking for a simple kitchen upgrade? Updating your sink&rsquo;s faucet is an excellent way to improve both the function and aesthetic of your kitchen. And if you&rsquo;re looking for an eye-catching vintage style with modern functionality, look no further than bridge faucets!</p>

9734

9735

9736<p>

9737&nbsp;</p>

9738

9739

9740<h2>

9741What is a Bridge Style Faucet?</h2>

9742

9743

9744<p>

9745A bridge faucet has two handles, one hot and one cold, that are connected by a horizontal pipe that also holds up the spout.<br />

9746

9747&nbsp;</p>

9748

9749

9750<p>

9751Unlike a single handle faucet that automatically adjusts temperature for you, a bridge faucet mixes hot and cold water together as you adjust each handle to your temperature preference.<br />

9752

9753&nbsp;</p>

9754

9755

9756<p>

9757The great thing about bridge faucets is that they are all one piece, only require two holes to install it instead of three, and don&rsquo;t require a deck plate to cover your counter. Overall, these faucets are narrower, making them a great space saver for smaller kitchens.</p>

9758

9759

9760<p>

9761&nbsp;</p>

9762

9763

9764<h2>

9765Types of Bridge Kitchen Faucets</h2>

9766

9767

9768<p>

9769You will find a variety of bridge kitchen faucets out there that differ in design, colors, finishes, and features. When looking at faucets, you&rsquo;ll want to consider the faucet mount, the style, and other add-on features.</p>

9770

9771

9772<p>

9773&nbsp;</p>

9774

9775

9776<h3>

9777Faucet Mounts</h3>

9778

9779

9780<p>

9781Bridge faucets are usually mounted one of two ways&mdash;to the deck or to the wall. When looking at these two mounts, make sure they match your new or existing sink before you purchase.</p>

9782

9783

9784<p>

9785&nbsp;</p>

9786

9787

9788<h4>

9789<span style="font-size:18px;">

9790<strong>

9791<em>

9792Deck Mount Bridge Faucets</em>

9793</strong>

9794</span>

9795</h4>

9796

9797

9798<p>

9799A deck mount is the most common type of mount for kitchen faucets. This type is mounted through holes in your countertop or sink. Deck mounts are more popular because they are easy to install and can be fixed by accessing the hardware from both above and below the sink.</p>

9800

9801

9802<p>

9803&nbsp;</p>

9804

9805

9806<h4>

9807<span style="font-size:18px;">

9808<em>

9809<strong>

9810Wall Mount Bridge Faucets</strong>

9811</em>

9812</span>

9813</h4>

9814

9815

9816<p>

9817A wall mount bridge faucet is certainly a great option when you&rsquo;re looking to save space. Plus, they add a unique design element.</p>

9818

9819

9820<p>

9821&nbsp;</p>

9822

9823

9824<p>

9825However, they are a little trickier to install. First, the water lines have to be run up behind the wall before you begin installation, which is not always recommended as a DIY project.</p>

9826

9827

9828<p>

9829&nbsp;</p>

9830

9831

9832<p>

9833Before you move any plumbing or drill holes into your wall, you need to carefully measure your placement to ensure the faucet can be installed high enough to allow enough room for washing dishes and other tasks. Then you also need to measure to ensure that water will dispense in about the middle of your sink.</p>

9834

9835

9836<p>

9837&nbsp;</p>

9838

9839

9840<h3>

9841Bridge Faucet Styles</h3>

9842

9843

9844<p>

9845Though bridge style kitchen faucets are known for their more traditional look, today you can find bridge faucets in a variety of modern styles and finishes. Here&rsquo;s a quick look at different bridge faucet styles.</p>

9846

9847

9848<p>

9849&nbsp;</p>

9850

9851

9852<p>

9853<strong>

9854Modern</strong>

9855&mdash;Polished chrome or vibrant stainless steel both offer a modernized look to the bridge look. Look for options with seamless, minimalist design with no extra details or raised designs like you find with traditional bridge faucets. Many modern designs also come in gold or black matte finishes.</p>

9856

9857

9858<p>

9859&nbsp;</p>

9860

9861

9862<p>

9863<strong>

9864Traditional</strong>

9865&mdash;Bridge kitchen faucets have been an idea since the times of the Romans. Traditional styles are derived from those earlier designs. They usually have beveled details and curves and are often oil-rubbed bronze.</p>

9866

9867

9868<p>

9869&nbsp;</p>

9870

9871

9872<p>

9873<strong>

9874Transitional</strong>

9875&mdash;Many bridge kitchen faucets take a blended approach between modern and traditional styles. Transitional styles have a combination of the clean lines you&rsquo;ll see in modern designs and the curves from traditional designs. These designs are a popular choice.</p>

9876

9877

9878<p>

9879&nbsp;</p>

9880

9881

9882<p>

9883<strong>

9884Industrial</strong>

9885&mdash;Industrial styles have clean lines mixed with curves like traditional, but rely on angular silhouettes to define the style. This style offers a hard-working look that adds a rugged touch but still feels modern.</p>

9886

9887

9888<p>

9889&nbsp;</p>

9890

9891

9892<h3>

9893Other Bridge Faucet Features and Add Ons</h3>

9894

9895

9896<p>

9897Bridge kitchen faucets offer show-stopping style in any kitchen, and many offer additional functionalities that make cleaning dishes easier than ever! Some are directly attached to the faucet while others will be an add-on installed close to the bridge.</p>

9898

9899

9900<p>

9901&nbsp;</p>

9902

9903

9904<p>

9905<strong>

9906Side Spray</strong>

9907&mdash;Yes, your bridge kitchen faucet can come with a side sprayer! Sprayers are great for helping clean sticky and dried-on messes from dishes or cleaning out the harder-to-reach corner of your kitchen sink.</p>

9908

9909

9910<p>

9911&nbsp;</p>

9912

9913

9914<p>

9915<strong>

9916Pull Down Spout</strong>

9917&mdash;Instead of installing a separate sprayer to the side of your faucet, bridge faucets can include a spout with a pull down sprayer. . It&rsquo;s usually attached to the faucet with a magnet for easy use. But don&rsquo;t worry! Your bridge faucet with a pull-down sprayer can still look traditional, even if it has modern magnetic, high-powered spray functionality.</p>

9918

9919

9920<p>

9921&nbsp;</p>

9922

9923

9924<p>

9925<strong>

9926Spout Rotation</strong>

9927&mdash;One of the most important functions in any faucet is the spout rotation. You want the water to reach any part of the sink you&rsquo;re going to use! Luckily, nearly every modern-day bridget faucet has a high-degree spout rotation to help you with any task.</p>

9928

9929

9930<p>

9931&nbsp;</p>

9932

9933

9934<h2>

9935FAQs About Bridge Faucets</h2>

9936

9937

9938<h3>

9939How Much Do Bridge Kitchen Faucets Cost?</h3>

9940

9941

9942<p>

9943You can find bridge kitchen faucets that are just over $200, but most are in the $600 to $1,100 range. More expensive options don&rsquo;t always mean they are the better choice because everything depends on the style, design, and functionality you are looking for.</p>

9944

9945

9946<p>

9947&nbsp;</p>

9948

9949

9950<h3>

9951Can I Put Bridge Kitchen Faucets in Other Rooms?</h3>

9952

9953

9954<p>

9955Yes! You can put these types of faucets at any sink in any room in your home. Just make sure to decide on deck or wall mounting first, and measure everything to make sure they will fit!</p>

9956

9957

9958<p>

9959&nbsp;</p>

9960

9961

9962<h3>

9963Why Do Some Bridge Faucets Cost Much More than Others?</h3>

9964

9965

9966<p>

9967Bridge faucets vary in price due to finishes, materials, and other add-ons (like a side spray) that they include. You may find budget options for bridge faucets, but often either the entire faucet is made from plastic or added sprayers are made from plastic instead of the metal used in the rest of the faucet. Over time, these won&rsquo;t hold up.</p>

9968

9969

9970<p>

9971&nbsp;</p>

9972

9973

9974<p>

9975Bridge faucets in the $1,000 range can be handmade and are usually made with higher-quality materials like copper, solid brass, and bronze. They often use durable ceramic valve pieces and some even have additional design technology and materials to prevent common leaks and increase fluidity and control.</p>

9976

9977

9978<p>

9979&nbsp;</p>

9980

9981

9982<p>

9983These options will last you for years, which is exactly what you want when you&#39;re investing in home upgrades.</p>

9984

9985

9986<p>

9987&nbsp;</p>

9988

9989

9990<h3>

9991Choose the Best One For You!</h3>

9992

9993

9994<p>

9995Now you have everything you need to know about bridge kitchen faucets! We hope the information we&rsquo;ve provided helps you select the perfect faucet.</p>

9996
